==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prætexta
<hw>Pr⟦ae⟧*tex"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pr⟦ae⟧text⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>Pr⟦ae⟧textas</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. (sc. <ets>toga</ets>), fr.
<ets>praetextus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praetexere</ets> to weave before,
to fringe, border; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>texere</ets> to
weave.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A white robe with a purple
border, worn by a Roman boy before he was entitled to wear the <xex>toga
virilis</xex>, or until about the completion of his fourteenth year, and
by girls until their marriage. It was also worn by magistrates and
priests.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

